<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911205-0076</DOCNO><DOCID>911205-0076.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Stewart Enterprises Inc.:   FTC Alleges Funeral Firm   Broke Price-Disclosure Rule</HL><DATE>12/05/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C2</SO><CO>   STEI</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>CONSUMER andamp; HOUSEHOLD SERVICES (CSV)CONSUMER AND HOUSEHOLD PRODUCTS AND SERVICES (HOU)</IN><GV>FEDERAL TRADE COMMISSION (FTC)</GV><RE>LOUISIANA (LA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Stewart Enterprises Inc. said the Federal Trade Commissionfiled a complaint stating that five of its Dallas funeralhomes had violated the funeral disclosure rule that typedprice lists must be disclosed to customers.   The New Orleans-based company said no specific evidencehad been given them by the FTC. A spokesman for Stewart saidthe alleged violations did not result from consumercomplaints but are the result of an investigation by the FTCthat began in September 1989.</LP><TEXT>   The trial is expected in about a year said the spokesman.The company said that it does not expect the outcome toadversely affect earnings and that it welcomes theopportunity to settle the matter.   Stewart Enterprises owns and operates funeral homes andcemeteries.</TEXT></DOC>